{
  "texts": [
    "The framework comprised a 3D convolutional neural network for each modality, with predictions combined using a late fusion strategy based on Dempster-Shafer theory.",
    "The results highlighted the most relevant modalities needed for accurate diagnosis, aligning with clinical practice, and showed that combining multiple modalities led to better overall results than using them individually.",
    "[9] Studies on Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) reveal their utility in data augmentation for mammography, allowing for creating more comprehensive training datasets that improve AI model performance.",
    "[10, 11] Additionally, AI-based image generation techniques are being used to produce synthetic breast cancer images, which help refine diagnostic tools and increase their robustness.",
    "[12, 13] These advancements underscore the significant impact of generative AI in improving early detection, diagnostic accuracy, and personalized treatment plans for breast cancer patients."
  ]
}